  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Recent evidence suggests that chronic pain is associated with abnormal connectivity between
      brain regions associated with the processing of pain. We aim to test the diagnostic power of
      resting state functional magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) to diagnose patients with chronic
      back pain. Using new methods of image acquisition and analysis we aim to develop a
      computational method to correctly classify patients and matched control subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
